By He Jiawen, southern weekend correspondent

Southern weekend intern, Ren Huanxin

Associate Editor | Henin Ho

"Do you have a mask? "

Who would have thought that by 2020, that phrase would have become a more common Chinese greeting than "did you eat? ". In the sudden outbreak of new pneumonia, "a cover hard to get" has become a true portrayal of the disaster.

February 14,2020, was the 20th day that Yang Yang led workers to work overtime. This is a medical mask enterprise in Hubei. The raw materials stored in the factory won't last three days. As the head of first-line production, Yang Yang made "hundreds of phone calls" in one night, trying to purchase raw materials from other provinces, but to no avail.

The Mask tragicomedy takes place in different time and space. The day before, almost 24 hours did not sleep Jiang Tao finally saw the "Wuling brand" mask batch shipment, daily output of 200 million. Auto Maker SAIC-GM-Wuling Automobile, whose company is a joint supplier, has joined the wave of cross border conversions.

The mask market has become an unusual place in a complex picture of society that has been suddenly pushed away by the epidemic. Some are seeking help, some are running scams, some are turning over a new leaf and some are turning to other businesses, some e-commerce companies have repeatedly offered medical aid, and some e-commerce companies are suspected of being involved in hot spots, and many local governments have imposed heavy controls on production, and in some places, there's been a medical holdup. Beauty and ugliness, in one side of the mask interweaves staged.

At present, in the first-line hospital, in the resumption of business, still spread the voice of a shortage of masks. And between the market and control, supply and demand figures in the final geometry, after the sudden increase in production, the market path is still unknown.

1
Face masks are in short supply, and friends circle sells them at high prices

1

###Face masks are in short supply, and friends circle sells them at high prices

Yang Yang was notified of the purchase and deployment of the masks by the local government on the day of the New Year twenty-nine. But the workers were already home for the holidays, and it was difficult to assemble them. It was not until the second day of the first lunar month that less than a third of the workers, paid three times as much, were recalled and barely started.

On January 29, the State Council issued an urgent notice to local governments to quickly organize mask manufacturers to resume work and resume production, and proposed that the material support group of the joint prevention and control mechanism under the State Council should uniformly manage and allocate masks and dispatch special dispatches to key enterprises.

According to the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, as of February 13, there were 60 special envoys stationed in enterprises stationed in 41 key enterprises in 13 provinces. The whole process of production, delivery and receiving forms a controllable and traceable closed loop, so that a large number of masks are sent to Wuhan in time.

Many merchants on Taobao and jd.com responded to southern weekend reporters that a large number of masks that had been photographed had been requisitioned. All masks were given priority in Wuhan and shipments were delayed.

One side is the government emergency relief masks, masks in short supply, on the other side is friends circle mask high-priced selling.

There weren't enough masks in the house, and on Feb. 1, Yang Yang asked a group of friends in the industry, all of whom said they were out of stock. WECHAT circle of friends, but before the sale of clothes, mask, do overseas in the sale of face masks. A loose disposable mask price from four to five yuan to ten yuan, or even tens of yuan have, and the price a day like, "like the stock" up.

In fact, Yang Yang knew that the cost of a mask is only 2030 cents, even during the epidemic, Labor, logistics costs, and other factors, will not be so premium.

The mask production needs the license to be complete, the medical mask also needs to have the medical device product registration certificate, the production license. Southern weekend reporters found that many friends circle high-priced sales of medical masks, medical equipment production license is marked over the code, can not see manufacturers and other key information; There are a variety of countries, a variety of brands of civilian masks to take the form of pre-sale. After the buyer pays, often can not deliver goods for a long time.

Chaos not only in small-scale wechat business, some e-commerce platform can not guarantee the arrival of goods. On February 14, the China Consumers' Association launched an investigation into the practice of "cutting orders" at the home of the dolphin, an e-commerce platform.

Many consumers have reported to the southern weekend reporter, the Dolphin home originally did not sell masks, borrow the epidemic, said a mask sales, induce consumers to download its APP, registration order, set off consumer personal information. Some even deduct consumer fees in the name of "freight" and so on.

On the same day, the Dolphin family responded via Weibo, saying that the order for the mask had been fully refunded. But for the "water in a basket" of consumers, no doubt a waste of time and energy. Southern weekend reporter calls Dolphin home to ask, as of press release did not reply.

Alibaba, spell Doddo and other e-commerce platforms also appeared on a number of stores selling fake and inferior masks incident. As of Feb. 4, Alibaba said it had intercepted and removed 570,000 suspicious masks and permanently cleared 15 illegal mask shops. On February 6, the E-COMMERCE company announced that it would launch a civil lawsuit against 10 companies that violated the rules.

Face masks have also become a top priority for local governments. On February 7, the court of Gangzha district, Nantong City, Jiangsu Province, tried the country's first epidemic prevention material fraud case through the Internet. The defendant, Zhang mou, was sentenced to one and a half years in prison and fined 10,000 yuan for publishing false information about the sale of face masks online. Wang Feng, the judge, told southern weekend that the fast track procedure could be used in cases where the sentence is less than three years, and the sentence is heavier than usual. It is during the period when the epidemic situation is being considered that the fraud of epidemic prevention materials should be given a heavier punishment.

Since then, not only Jiangsu, Zhejiang, Heilongjiang, Xinjiang, Sichuan and other places have been sentenced for mask fraud or the sale of counterfeit products. As of press time, the latest case is in Sichuan. On February 19, a Zizhong County court sentenced the defendant, he mou, to five years in prison and fined him RMB20,000.

2
The government is doing everything it can to bring businesses back from the dead

2

###The government is doing everything it can to bring businesses back from the dead

"with the resumption of work during the Spring Festival, the supply of raw materials upstream is not a big problem, " a source from the China Medical Device Industry Association, which is in charge of the mask manufacturers, told southern weekend, it may also face problems such as the doubling of labor costs and poor logistics. However, "the government is trying to deploy whatever thread is missing" .

"If there is a shortage of raw materials or a shortage of workers, the government will try to find a way to buy it at a higher price and then subsidize it, " an official from the Municipal Bureau of Industry and Information Technology in Guangxi told southern weekend

Government departments have been racking their brains to get mask manufacturers back to work, indirectly bringing back a number of companies that have long since stopped production or are on the verge of bankruptcy.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, the relevant personnel of the Medical Devices Division of the Changping District Market Supervision Bureau were instructed to screen out enterprises with production capacity of epidemic prevention materials. Eventually, a company was found that could make masks, but they had been out of production for five years. However, it took just 12 days for production to resume.

Suzhou Gangsong Protection Technology Co. , Ltd. . An employee told southern weekend that the company originally entered bankruptcy liquidation procedures in December 2019. But on Feb. 3,2020, the company resumed production, with the first line producing 20,000 KN95 masks and three more coming on stream. On the same day, a 10-year-old mask factory in Bazhong, 1,600 km away, reopened after 96 hours of preparation. In Weihai, Shandong Province, Weihai Hongyu non-woven Products Co. , Ltd. entered bankruptcy reorganization in April 2016. On January 27, the Economic and Technological Development Zones in Weihai set aside $3m to help the company get back to work quickly.

On Feb. 3, the first day of trading, shares of Jett rose 108.54 percent. Little known is that Bayfer, a subsidiary of Gert Bio, which makes face masks, has been losing money. Yuan Jianhua, chairman of jade bio, previously told the media that the company's mask was originally intended to combat smog, and that the parent company had already decided to go through the cancellation process because of the reduced smog. It has now withdrawn the cancellation application.

3
Cross-border transfer of production, self-help

3

###Cross-border transfer of production, self-help

Some local governments have encouraged enterprises to speed up the production of face masks and protective clothing by expanding production, transferring production and building new ones.

Putian, Fujian Province, is a typical example.

Li Jianhui, the city's mayor, calls on Putian businesses to "save their own skin" . Putian resident population of nearly three million, in the face of the resumption of work, school peak, the daily use of more than 1.5 million masks, relying on external deployment, social donations is a drop in the bucket.

On February 1, the Industry and Information Bureau of Putian issued a "call to transfer production order" , giving a timetable for subsidies. 60 per cent of the value of equipment purchased before 6 February and 50 per cent before 15 February will be provided for equipment installed and produced.

This is a top-down mobilization.

Since late January, the meeting of the Central Leading Group for the response to the epidemic has called on all localities to quickly organize the production of medical protective clothing, face masks, medical goggles and negative pressure ambulances, and for these enterprises to provide tax, financial and other support policies.

Putian is famous for its shoes. Under the direct direction of the Putian Government, the Putian Bureau of Industry and Information Technology has joined forces with shoe associations and local producers of diapers to form a "mask production team" . Xu Weijing, head of the General Management Office of Li Nu shoe industry, told southern weekend that in-house people nicknamed the "Group" the "Mask Research Institute" and Zhang Zhihong, director of the Putian Bureau of Industry and Information Technology, became the "president of the Mask Research Institute. ".

It is not difficult for a company to change its business. Under normal circumstances, depending on the type of production and degree of automation, a mask production line construction costs between 100,000 to 400,000 yuan. A 24-hour production line, the production capacity of about 50,000, a high degree of automation, up to 100,000.

Raw materials for production are provided by the government, and the Footwear Industry Association is in charge of logistics. Even so, production was at a standstill because of the time limit for resuming work. Workers at Putian companies were not allowed to return to work until February 10, so they had to call in remaining and peripheral workers to resume work.

At present, the larger problem is the shortage of protective clothing, head cover, foot cover and so on.

"In general, the production of masks for civilian use is not high, in fact, the threshold is not high, the degree of automation is high, and the overall conversion speed is very fast. Wuling only took three days to get off the line, " Jiang Tao explained.

The first step is to ensure a clean workshop, which is readily available for many manufacturers of footwear, baby products or women's products.

Even though the production environment of medical masks requires a 100,000 level of cleanliness (that is, no more than 100,000 particles larger than 0.5 microns per cubic meter) , the production of diapers requires a 300,000 level of cleanliness. As a result, the Putian Company that makes diapers, Le Cheng Household Products Co. , Ltd. (Le Cheng Life) , has also shifted production, but for the time being only produces civilian masks.

In addition to the 100,000 level of cleanliness in the workshop, there is also the need for oxirane sterilization. It's more complicated, it's longer. The production cycle is about one week longer than that of a commercial mask, depending on the killing equipment. Therefore, most of the conversion of production enterprises are civilian masks.

Secondly, the raw materials and equipment in place, such as non-woven, melt-blown cloth and mask machine.

In addition, for the production of masks for civilian use, we must apply for "production license" , "business license" , "hygiene license" , "product qualification certificate" , etc. , the production of medical masks should apply for "medical device product registration certificate" and "medical device production license" from relevant departments at the provincial level.

Many industry-related people said that with more and more enterprises to resume production, cross-border transfer of production, especially the entry of large industrial enterprises, raw materials, equipment supply has become very tight.

4
How big is the breach

4

###How big is the breach

On Feb. 13, the same day that Wuling Masks were mass-produced, National Development and Reform Commission data showed that daily production of masks in Hubei Province jumped from 45,000 on Feb. 2 to 158,000 on Feb. 11, henan, Zhejiang and other places increased from zero output to 14,000 and 100,000 respectively.

Still, no one knows exactly how big China's mask gap is.

The world is facing a chronic shortage of face masks, gloves and the like as a result of the personal protective equipment outbreak, and demand is now 100 times the normal level, the World Health Organization said Feb. 7, prices are more than 20 times normal.

The next day, huachuang securities, based on a nationwide demand analysis of the resumption of work, China's secondary and tertiary industries employed a total of 530 million people, or one per day, the daily need of 530 million masks. In extreme cases, 238 million are needed each day in the secondary sector of the economy, health care, and transportation industries alone.

But Lei Limin, vice president of the China Textile Business Association, said that because the actual situation is changing from day to day, it is difficult to give an exact figure for the demand and the gap for face masks in China, but what is certain is that the demand and the gap are both very large.

The daily demand for masks in China has exceeded 150 million, an industry source told southern weekend on condition of anonymity. Demand is likely to double with the resumption of work. But he did not elaborate on how that would be measured.

It is foreseeable that, on the one hand, the amount of face masks used by hospitals and other front-line anti-epidemic units will not decrease, on the other hand, the number of face masks used by enterprises returning to work will increase substantially. Coupled with the daily travel demand of ordinary citizens, face masks will not be available, demand will only increase.

China is the world's largest producer and exporter of face masks, accounting for half of the world's annual output. On Jan. 23, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology announced that China's maximum production capacity for face masks is more than 20 million a day.

During the Spring Festival, the actual daily production of masks on January 25(the first day of the Lunar New Year) was only 8 million. As of February 3, there were 14.806 million in 22 key provinces, or 67 percent of the total, according to the Capacity utilization. As of February 11,94 percent of the nation's mask manufacturers were Capacity utilization.

According to the association's data, the production capacity of face masks is being released gradually. With the increase of production capacity, it is estimated that nearly 200 million face masks will be produced every day by the end of February, it is expected to alleviate the anxiety of shortage of masks to some extent.

And a person close to the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology told southern weekend that the actual production capacity is higher than this figure. On the one hand, because many private micro, small and medium-sized enterprises are among the mask manufacturers, there are even some flexible forms of "one household and one factory" (that is, small workshops) , which were not previously covered by the statistics of the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology. On the other hand, there may be underreporting and under-reporting of capacity.

Fortunately, companies that changed production during this period were registered by the government, and their production capacity could be recorded as accurately as possible in official statistics, said the municipal industry and Information Bureau official.

"To count capacity, companies will want to underreport to the local engineering and information authorities and keep some for the market, while the local government will want to underreport and keep some for itself. "

The Ministry of Industry and Information Technology said the relevant people, this is the government's unified allocation of resources is very disadvantageous.

5
What's the profit margin on a mask

5

###What's the profit margin on a mask

Under government control, a number of enterprises have said that mask production costs because of each channel, ups and downs of great, difficult to measure profits.

Yang Yang said companies are allowed to charge only a small profit on government purchase prices. The Enterprise shall report the price of raw materials and labor cost of the goods, and submit a consolidated financial statement to the government for accounting. "If the cost of producing the masks is $1 each, the government will allow perhaps 20 per cent of the profit and take them away at $1.20 each. "

Li Nu shoes industry, Lecheng life and other enterprises said the current production costs rose, but the specific data has not been measured.

Now unified by the government acquisition, Le Cheng living production mask acquisition price of 1.7 yuan per unit, and the acquisition price in other areas are also generally within the range of 0.5-1.5 yuan.

The Chinese Medical Device Industry Association said the government allows companies to have a reasonable profit margin at the cost of each batch of production additional profits. "It's still profitable for the companies that make the masks. At least this half year or this year is an opportunity to make a profit. "

Prices vary from place to place. In terms of government fixed-point prices, Shanghai's uniform price is 0.45 yuan per piece, Xuchang's 1.3 yuan per piece in Henan, Xiantao's single-use medical mask in Hubei is not allowed to exceed 1.20 yuan per piece, and the price of non-medical mask is not allowed to exceed 1.00 yuan per piece, the retail price of each mask in Huanggang is $0.65 to $0.80.

Southern weekend reporters visited some pharmacies and stores in Beijing. Many officials said that compared with some unreliable wechat merchants, retailers who actually sell masks are reluctant to sell them. Hard to buy, expensive to buy, slow logistics, but also to bear market risk, let them on a mask only a few cents profit prohibitive.

When the outbreak broke out, it was still difficult to control the price rise, even though on the night of January 21, Taobao's official microblog posted a statement that it would not allow the price of face masks to rise.

High premium masks are not necessarily fake. An industry source told southern weekend that mask manufacturers usually try to keep some of it for dealers. Once the epidemic is over, the government will no longer buy the masks in unison, but will have to rely on distributors to sell them. "That's why some companies are overstating their capacity and there's room for a premium in the market for masks. "

A supermarket purchasing official in Beijing told southern weekend that regular supermarkets would not raise prices for no reason. "If the suppliers go up as much, we won't lose money if we don't go up as much. And the government won't supply them. "

Beijing's Fengtai District and Tianjin's Jinnan district's market regulators have imposed fines of up to $3M -- or as much as $100m -- on pharmacies in the region for allegedly inflating the prices of face masks.

There are also controversial tickets. On February 5, Huakang pharmacy in Honghu, Hubei Province, was fined more than 40,000 yuan for selling one-off face masks at a price of 0.6 yuan, or 1 yuan, which exceeded the city's 15 percent limit.

However, in the public opinion atmosphere that the netizen cries for its Qu Qu, after this case Investigates Afresh, execute punishment no longer.

"normal price increases should not be banned, nor should they be punished by a one-size-fits-all increase, " Lu Ming, a professor at the Shanghai Jiao Tong University, told the media during the "one-yuan mask" incident. This also caused some economists to the market mechanism view. Li Huiwen, a professor at Beijing University of International Business and Economics, wrote: The market is an efficient coordination mechanism for information exchange, and it is very robust. At a time when the COVID-19 epidemic is spreading rapidly, it is particularly important to fully recognize and respect this value of the market, and to protect the environment in which the market mechanism works.

On February 15th Yang Yang finally found an upstream supplier in the provinces, but logistics costs were three times higher. Still, as of press time, Yang Yang had not been notified of the shipment -- until the local government requisitioned all of the upstream supplier's raw materials for quarantine purposes.
